Then, we use the `proc lifetest` procedure to calculate the length of survival using the exponential distribution. We specify the `data` option to indicate the name of the input data set, and the `method` option to specify the type of distribution we want to use. 

We use the `time` statement to specify the end date variable and the censoring variable, and the `strata` statement to stratify the analysis by drug addict status. 

The output of this code will include the survival estimates, the survival function plots, and the hazard function plots for each stratum.
